INSERT INTO `recipe_instructions` VALUES (1,'A-Plus Italian Olive Oil Balsamic Bread Dip','Place the garlic, balsamic vinegar, olive oil, red pepper flakes, rosemary, and salt and pepper into a shallow bowl in that order. To serve, spoon small amount onto bread.'),(1,'Absolutely Delicious Stuffed Calamari','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Rinse the calamari tubes and pat dry.'),(1,'Ada (Adai)','Place the chana dal, urad dal, moong dal, and rice into a large bowl and cover with several inches of cool water; allow to soak 8 hours to overnight.'),(1,'Affogato','Place gelato in an old fashioned glass and pour freshly brewed espresso over top. Serve immediately.'),(1,'Air Fryer Chicken Katsu with Homemade Katsu Sauce','Prepare sauce: Whisk ketchup, soy sauce, brown sugar, sherry, Worcestershire sauce, and garlic together in a bowl until sugar has dissolved. Set katsu sauce aside.'),(1,'Air Fryer Tonkatsu','Make sauce: Whisk together ketchup, soy sauce, brown sugar, sherry, Worcestershire sauce, and garlic in a medium bowl until sugar is dissolved. Set sauce aside.'),(1,'Akki Rotti','Cover the mung beans with the water and refrigerate overnight. The next day, drain the beans and reserve the soaking water.'),(1,'Al Capone Roast','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),(1,'Ali\'s Amazing Bruschetta','Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).'),(1,'Alicia\'s Aloo Gobi','Heat oil in a large pot on medium-high heat and add onion. Cook until softened, about 4 minutes, then stir in garlic and cumin. Continue to cook until onion begins to brown.'),(1,'Almond Ricotta Cake','Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Grease an 8-inch springform pan and line with parchment paper.'),(1,'Almost Tuscan Sausage and Kale Soup','Heat oil in a large stockpot over medium heat until the oil shimmers; cook and stir onion, garlic, red pepper flakes, and black pepper until onion is translucent, 10 to 15 minutes.'),(1,'Aloo Gobi','Heat 2 tablespoons of oil over medium-high heat in a large pot. Fry cumin seeds for a few seconds until they turn golden brown and begin to pop. Reduce heat to medium, stir in the onion, and cook until lightly browned. Stir in serrano pepper and ginger; fry for 1 minute. Season with coriander, paprika, turmeric, cayenne, and garam masala; cook for 30 seconds until fragrant.'),(1,'Aloo Gobi Masala (Cauliflower and Potato Curry)','Place the cauliflower in a large, microwave-safe dish; cook in microwave on High for 3 minutes. Transfer the cauliflower to a bowl and set aside. Put the potatoes in the dish and cook in the microwave on High for 4 minutes. Pour into the bowl with the cauliflower.'),(1,'Aloo Paratha','Place a steamer insert into a saucepan and fill with water to just below the bottom of the steamer. Bring water to a boil. Add potatoes, cover, and steam until tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from the heat.'),(1,'Aloo Phujia','Lightly brown onion in oil in a medium size skillet.'),(1,'Amazing Mussels','Melt butter in a large stockpot over medium heat. Add garlic and shallots, and cook, stirring constantly, until lightly browned. Add a splash of the beef broth, jalapeno, and red chile pepper, and simmer for a few minutes to blend the flavors.'),(1,'American Lasagna','Gather all ingredients.'),(1,'American-Italian Pasta Salad','Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add fusilli and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, 10 to 13 minutes.'),(1,'Americano Cocktail','Add ice to a tall glass. Pour in Campari and vermouth. Stir and top with soda water. Squeeze a twist of orange peel over the drink and drop it in.'),(1,'Ancient Roman Cheesecake (Savillum)','Preheat an oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Pour some water into a small, oven proof bowl, and place into the oven. Arrange the bay leaves over the bottom of the springform pan to cover.'),(1,'Angel Hair with Feta and Sun-Dried Tomatoes','Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook angel hair pasta in boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, 4 to 5 minutes. Drain and return pasta to the pot.'),(1,'Anisette Toast','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt together in a bowl; set aside. Grease 2 baking sheets.'),(1,'Antipasto on a Stick','Thread ingredients onto toothpicks in the following order: salami roll, mozzarella cube, olive, tomato half, artichoke heart, and basil leaf. Arrange toothpicks on a serving platter and drizzle olive oil over top.'),(1,'Antipasto Pasta Salad','Make the salad: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add shell pasta and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 9 minutes. Drain, run under cold water to cool pasta, and drain again.'),(1,'Antipasto Salad','Combine Genoa and soppressata salamis, provolone, mozzarella, tomatoes, and artichokes in a bowl. Slice roasted red peppers and add them to the bowl with about 3 tablespoons juice from the red pepper jar. Mix in chopped olives.'),(1,'Artichoke Bruschetta','Preheat the broiler.'),(1,'Artichoke Salad','Start the salad: Spray a large skillet with cooking spray and set over medium heat. Add rice and vermicelli mix and sautÃ© until vermicelli is golden brown, 2 to 4 minutes. Slowly stir in water and seasoning packet; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer until rice is tender, 15 to 20 minutes.'),(1,'Artichoke Spinach Lasagna','Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a 9x13 inch baking dish with cooking spray.'),(1,'Ashley\'s Chicken Katsu with Tonkatsu Sauce','For the sauce, stir together the Worcestershire sauce, ketchup, and soy sauce, and a pinch of pepper to taste. Set aside.'),(1,'Asparagus Wrapped in Crisp Prosciutto','Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil, and coat with olive oil.'),(1,'Atta (Whole Wheat) Halwa','Melt the ghee in a heavy-bottomed skillet over medium heat; cook the cashews and raisins in the melted ghee until the raisins plump and the cashews are lightly browned, about 5 minutes. Remove the cashews and raisins from the pan with a slotted spoon and set aside. Add the flour to the pan and roast till brown and nutty, about 10 minutes.'),(1,'Aunt Anne\'s Sesame Cookies','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),(1,'Authentic and Easy Shrimp Curry','Heat the oil in a wok or large saucepan over nearly high heat. Add the onions; cook and stir until browned. Mix in the curry leaves, then season with the ginger garlic paste, coriander and salt. Cook and stir for 1 minute.'),(1,'Authentic Chicken Tikka Masala','Make the chicken: Combine yogurt, garam masala, paprika, black pepper, salt, cayenne pepper, and coriander in a large bowl. Add chicken strips and toss to coat. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 2 hours.'),(1,'Authentic Italian Rice Pudding','Mix milk, rice, 1/2 of the sugar, vanilla extract, and salt together in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Bring to a boil.'),(1,'Authentic Japanese Scallop Soup with Ramen Noodles','Bring a medium pot of water to a boil. Add ramen and cook, breaking up noodles as they soften, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 3 minutes. Drain, rinse with cold water, and drain again. Divide noodles between two soup bowls.'),(1,'Authentic Miso Soup','Heat water in a large pot over low heat. Add kombu and cook until just simmering. Stir in bonito flakes, then remove dashi stock from the heat. Let dashi sit, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Strain and set aside.'),(1,'Authentic Pizza Margherita','Stir flour and 1 teaspoon salt in a bowl. Set aside.'),(1,'Authentic Taralli','Combine flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, oil, and wine in a stand mixer. Mix ingredients using the paddle attachment until a ball forms. Switch to the dough hook and knead dough for 10 minutes.'),(1,'Authentic Tiramisu','Beat together egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, brandy, and 1 tablespoon espresso in a bowl with an electric mixer until smooth, 2 to 3 minutes. Add mascarpone cheese; beat until well blended, 3 to 5 minutes.'),(1,'Authentic Yakisoba','Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Cook soba in boiling water, stirring occasionally, until noodles are tender yet firm to the bite, 5 to 8 minutes. Drain noodles and rinse with cold water. Set aside.'),(1,'Avocado Caprese Salad','Arrange tomato slices on a serving platter. Lay 1 avocado slice on top of each tomato, and top with fresh mozzarella. Drizzle olive oil, then balsamic vinegar over the tops, and season with salt and pepper.'),(1,'Bagna Calda (Italian Garlic-Anchovy-Sardine Appetizer)','Place canola oil in a skillet and heat over medium heat. Stir in garlic; cook until golden brown, about 5 minutes. Add butter, anchovies, and sardines; cook and stir until well blended, 10 to 15 minutes. Serve warm.'),(1,'Bagna Cauda','Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Stir in garlic and cook until tender. Reduce heat to low. Mix in anchovy filets and heavy cream. Cook and stir until thickened. Remove from heat, cover and chill in the refrigerator approximately 2 hours.'),(1,'Baguette Pizza','Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(1,'Baingan Bharta (Eggplant Curry)','Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).'),(1,'Baked Caprese Crostini','Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).'),(1,'Baked Italian Chicken Thighs','Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(1,'Baked Orange Roughy, Italian-Style','Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Coat a medium baking dish with nonstick spray.'),(1,'Baked Pasta','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.'),(1,'Baked Penne with Italian Sausage','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),(1,'Baked Polenta with Fresh Tomatoes and Parmesan','Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Grease an 8x8 inch baking dish.'),(1,'Baked Potato Pizza','Preheat an oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Scrub and dry potatoes, then prick several times with a fork and place onto a baking sheet.'),(1,'Baked Shrimp Scampi','Place shrimp into a saucepan, cover with water to a depth of 2 inches over shrimp, and bring to a boil. Cover pan and cook until shrimp are pink, 2 to 3 minutes; drain.'),(1,'Baked Spaghetti I','Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add spaghetti, and cook for 8 to 10 minutes, or until al dente. Drain, and set aside.'),(1,'Baked Tomatoes Oregano','Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Coat a shallow baking dish with cooking spray.'),(1,'Baked Ziti IV','Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook pasta in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes, or until al dente; drain.'),(1,'Balsamic Bruschetta','Gather all ingredients.'),(1,'Balsamic Chicken','Whisk together chicken broth, balsamic vinegar, sugar, Italian seasoning, and garlic in a bowl. Place chicken breasts in marinade; let marinate for 10 minutes on each side.'),(1,'Balsamic Roasted Pork Loin','Combine vinegar and steak seasoning in a medium bowl; stir until seasoning is dissolved. Stir in olive oil until combined.'),(1,'Banana Chai Bread','In a medium bowl mix together flour, baking powder, and salt.'),(1,'Banana Lassi','Blend bananas, yogurt, milk, ice cubes, and sugar together in a blender until smooth.'),(1,'Bangaladumpa (Potato) Upma Koora','Place the potatoes into a large pot and cover with salted water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain and allow to steam dry for a minute or two. Remove and discard the skins; roughly mash the potatoes into coarse chunks. Set aside.'),(1,'Bangan ka Bhurta (Indian Eggplant)','Preheat the oven broiler. Place eggplant in a roasting pan, and broil 5 minutes, turning occasionally, until about 1/2 the skin is scorched.'),(1,'Basic Indian Curry with Paneer','Heat oil in a large pan over medium heat. Cook and stir onion in hot oil until onion has softened and turned translucent, about 5 minutes. Reduce heat to low and continue cooking and stirring until onion is very tender and dark brown, about 20 minutes more. Stir in garlic and ginger; cook for 1 minute.'),(1,'Basil Pesto Bread Rounds','Preheat oven on broiler setting. Arrange bread slices in a single layer on a cookie sheet. Place under broiler for 5 to 8 minutes, or until lightly toasted on one side. Watch carefully to ensure they don\'t burn. Remove from oven, and flip bread slices so that the toasted side is on the bottom.'),(1,'Batata Nu Shak (Potato Curry)','Heat the oil in a skillet over medium heat. Fry the cumin seeds, mustard seeds, fennel seeds, and red chile peppers in the oil until the seeds begin to splutter. Stir the asafoetida powder into the mixture. Add the onion, ginger, and turmeric; cook and stir for a few minutes. Add the tomato and simmer until the tomatoes are soft. Sprinkle the ground cumin, coriander, and ground red pepper over the mixture.'),(1,'BBQ Chicken Pizza','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),(1,'BBQ Pulled Pork Pizza','Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).'),(1,'Bean Soup with Kale','Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Cook and stir onion and garlic in hot oil until soft. Add kale; cook and stir until wilted. Add 3 cups broth, 2 cups beans, tomatoes, herb seasoning, salt, and pepper; bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.'),(1,'Beef Kushiyaki','In a bowl, mix the mirin, garlic, soy sauce, monosodium glutamate, and sugar; stir to dissolve the sugar. Place the beef and green onions into the marinade, stir to coat with marinade, and allow to stand for 30 minutes. Soak bamboo skewers in water.'),(1,'Beef Teppanyaki','Combine soy sauce, mirin, garlic powder, black pepper, and ground ginger together in a bowl. Add sliced beef and mix well. Leave to marinate at least 1 hour.'),(1,'Beef Vindaloo','Whisk the vinegar, garlic paste, ginger paste, yogurt, salt, black pepper, and red pepper together in a mixing bowl. Mix in the beef cubes until evenly coated. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap, and marinate in the refrigerator overnight (or at least 30 minutes).'),(1,'Beefy Baked Ravioli','Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).'),(1,'Bell Pepper, Tomato, and Potato Indian Curry','Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over low heat. Stir mustard seed into hot oil; cook and stir until seeds start to crackle, about 30 seconds. Stir garlic, green chile pepper, curry leaves, cumin seed, and asafoetida powder into mustard seeds; cook and stir until the garlic is fragrant and beginning to turn golden, 3 to 5 minutes.'),(1,'Bengali Chicken Curry with Potatoes','Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir the onions in the hot oil until translucent, about 5 minutes. Add the ginger-garlic paste and continue cooking another 5 minutes. Reduce heat to medium; stir the tomatoes into the mixture and cook until the tomatoes are pulpy, 5 to 10 minutes. Season with the cayenne pepper, curry powder, garam masala, turmeric, and cumin; cook and stir another 5 minutes.'),(1,'Besan (Gram Flour) Halwa','Bring the milk and water to a simmer in a saucepan over medium-low heat; stir the cardamom into the mixture. Set aside.'),(1,'Besan Laddu','Stir the chickpea flour and clarified butter together in a saucepan over medium-low heat until the mixture smells toasty, about 10 minutes. Set aside until cool enough to handle.'),(1,'Best Bruschetta Ever','In a medium bowl, mix tomatoes, dried basil, Parmesan cheese, olive oil, garlic, seasoning salt and ground black pepper. Cover and chill in the refrigerator 8 hours, or overnight, before serving.'),(1,'Best Caprese Skewers','Gather all ingredients.'),(1,'Best Darn Minestrone Soup Around','In a large stock pot over medium heat, stir and cook onions in butter until soft. Add broth, mixed vegetables, kidney beans, tomatoes, spinach, and tomato paste; simmer gently for 1 1/2 hours.'),(1,'Best Ever Party Appetizer','Slice goat cheese into one inch pieces and place in a single layer on a large platter. Sprinkle olive oil, sun-dried tomatoes, black olives, basil and rosemary over the cheese.'),(1,'Best Ever Slow Cooker Italian Beef Roast','Place beef chuck roast into a slow cooker and scatter onion quarters around the meat. Pour the beef broth over the meat and sprinkle the au jus mix, Italian salad dressing mix, salt, and black pepper over the roast.'),(1,'Best Italian Sausage Soup','In a large pot, cook sausage over medium heat until brown. Remove with a slotted spoon, and drain on paper towels. Drain fat from pan, reserving 3 tablespoons.'),(1,'Best Lasagna with Ricotta Bechamel','Prepare meat sauce: Heat a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add ground sirloin and sausage; cook and stir until browned and crumbly, about 8 minutes. Drain and set aside.'),(1,'Best Vegan Naan','Mix water and sugar in a bowl; whisk until dissolved. Sprinkle yeast over water; let stand until yeast softens and begins to form a creamy foam, about 5 minutes.'),(1,'Bettie\'s Lasagna Roll Ups','Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook lasagna noodles for 5 to 8 minutes, or until just slightly underdone; drain and rinse.'),(1,'Bhindi Masala (Spicy Okra Curry)','Place the okra in a large, microwave-safe dish; cook in microwave on High for 6 minutes.'),(1,'Biddy\'s Butternut Squash and Turkey Lasagna','Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(1,'Biryani with Yogurt Marinated Chicken','Mix yogurt, garlic, ginger, garam masala, turmeric, and salt together in a bowl. Add chicken breast; toss to coat evenly. Cover bowl and marinate chicken in the refrigerator, at least 1 hour.'),(1,'Biscotti','Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease two cookie sheets or line with parchment paper.'),(1,'Black Chana with Potato','Sort and clean chickpeas and wash them under cold water; drain. Combine chickpeas, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and baking soda in a large bowl; add 1 quart water. Soak chickpeas for 24 hours; drain.'),(1,'Black Olive and Rosemary Focaccia','Stir together the water, sugar, and yeast until dissolved, allow to stand for 5 minutes. Stir in 2 tablespoons olive oil, 1/4 cup rosemary, flour, and salt until a dough forms. Turn onto a lightly floured surface, and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. Gently knead in the black olives during the last few minutes of kneading. Place into a lightly oiled bowl, cover with a towel, and let rise in a warm place until almost doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.'),(1,'Black Sesame Pudding','Stir water and gelatin together in a bowl until gelatin dissolves.'),(1,'Bob\'s Stuffed Banana Peppers','Cut off the tops of peppers. Remove ribs and seeds; rinse peppers. Chop edible portion of the tops; set aside.'),(1,'Bocconcini Salad','In a large salad bowl, combine the mozzarella, cherry tomatoes, bell pepper, celery, endive and arugula.'),(1,'Bolognese Sauce','Warm oil in a large skillet over medium heat. SautÃ© onion, bacon, and garlic in hot oil until bacon is browned and crisp, about 10 minutes. Use a slotted spoon to transfer bacon mixture to a paper towel-lined plate to drain; set aside.'),(1,'Bolognese Tagliatelle','Cook pancetta in a pan over medium heat until it has released its fat and is crisp, 7 to 8 minutes. Add carrots, celery, and onions; cook until vegetables soften and onions are translucent, 7 to 8 minutes. Set aside.'),(1,'Bomba Calabrese (Spicy Calabrian Pepper Spread)','Place mushrooms, onion, and eggplant into bowl of a food processor. Pulse on and off until very finely chopped but not liquefied, 8 to 10 pulses.'),(1,'Bombay Chicken and Rice','Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(1,'Bombay Potatoes','Place cubed potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water. Cover with a lid and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Once water is boiling, cook until potatoes are just tender, 5 to 10 minutes. Drain well and set aside.'),(1,'Boneless Chicken Cacciatore','Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until no longer pink in the middle, 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in celery, onion, bell peppers, garlic, tomatoes, tomato juice, tomato paste, parsley, salt, basil, oregano, marjoram, and black pepper. Cover and let simmer until vegetables are no longer crispy, about 10 minutes.'),(1,'Bow Ties with Sausage, Tomatoes, and Cream','Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook pasta in boiling water until al dente, 8 to 10 minutes; drain.'),(1,'Bracciole (Flank Steak Rolls)','Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat; cook and stir onion in the hot oil until tender, about 10 minutes. Season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon pepper.'),(1,'Bread and Butter Pizza','Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).Â Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.'),(1,'Bread Machine Pizza Dough','Put beer, butter, sugar, salt, flour, and yeast in a bread machine in the order recommended by the manufacturer. Select Dough setting, and press Start.'),(1,'Bread Machine Thin Crust Pizza Dough','Gather all ingredients.'),(1,'Breakfast Pizza','Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(1,'Brick-Oven Pizza (Brooklyn Style)','Make the dough: Pour warm water into a large bowl, then sprinkle yeast over the top. Let stand for 5 minutes. Stir in cold water and salt. Stir in flour, 1 cup at a time until incorporated.'),(1,'Brinjal (Eggplant) in Coconut Milk','Season brinjal with 1/4 teaspoon chile powder, 1/8 teaspoon turmeric powder, and salt; set aside until flavors to set, 3 to 4 minutes.'),(1,'Broccoli Garlic Angel Hair Pasta','Heat butter and oil in a large skillet over medium heat until hot. Add garlic and cook, stirring often, until soft but not browned, 1 to 2 minutes. Sprinkle in pepper flakes and season with salt.'),(1,'Broiled Mochi with Nori Seaweed','Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (275 degrees C).'),(1,'Bruschetta al Pomodoro','Preheat the oven broiler.'),(1,'Bruschetta Salad','Combine tomatoes, mozzarella cheese, bagel chips, basil, red onion, olive oil, red wine vinegar, garlic, basil, salt, and black pepper together in a bowl; toss until evenly combined. Refrigerate until chilled, 15 to 30 minutes.'),(1,'Bruschetta with Cheese','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),(1,'Bucatini All\'Amatriciana','Fill a large pot with lightly salted water and bring to a rolling boil. Stir in bucatini and return to a boil. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until bucatini is tender, about 11 minutes. Drain.'),(1,'Bucatini Pasta with Shrimp and Anchovies','Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente; drain.'),(1,'Buffalo Chicken Lasagna','Place chicken in a single layer in a large pot and add enough chicken stock to cover; season with paprika, 1 teaspoon salt, and cayenne pepper. Bring stock to a boil, reduce heat to medium, and simmer until chicken is no longer pink in the center, 15 to 20 minutes. Shred chicken.'),(1,'Buffalo Chicken Sushi Roll','Mix chicken and hot sauce in a bowl and toss to coat.'),(1,'Buffalo-Style Chicken Pizza','Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).'),(1,'Butter Chicken (Murgh Makhani)','Make a spice mix by combining garam masala, tandoori masala, curry powder, cumin, cardamom, cayenne, salt, and black pepper in a small bowl; set aside.'),(1,'Buttermilk-Battered Calamari','Heat oil in a saucepan or deep-fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),(1,'Butternut Squash Coconut Curry','Combine squash, water, olive oil, salt, mustard seeds, cumin seeds, cayenne pepper, and turmeric in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until squash is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.'),(1,'Butterscotch Budino','Combine brown sugar, salt, and water in a deep, heavy-bottomed saucepan and place over medium-high heat. Bring to a boil; cook until caramel is very dark, and bubbles appear, 7 to 10 minutes. Immediately turn off the heat.'),(1,'Cabbage and Smoked Sausage Soup','Heat the vegetable oil in a large pot over medium heat, and cook the onion until lightly browned. Place sausage in the pot, and pour in water. Mix in cabbage, carrots, celery, rice, beans, tomato sauce, and crushed tomatoes. Dissolve bouillon in the mixture. Season with salt, bay leaf, and thyme. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, and cook at least 1 hour, until vegetables are tender and rice is cooked.'),(1,'Cabbage Curry','Place a large skillet or wok over high heat. Heat oil and butter until smoking. Add onion, carrot, and garlic; cook and stir until onion begins to soften, about 1 minute. Add cabbage, coconut, and curry powder; stir fry for 2 more minutes.'),(1,'Cabbage Lasagna','Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir ground beef, onion, and garlic in the hot skillet until meat is browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain and discard grease. Add carrots and mushrooms. Add tomatoes and break up using a fork. Add basil, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, thyme, and nutmeg. Reduce heat and simmer meat sauce for 30 minutes.'),(1,'Calamari','Heat oil in a deep-fryer or large saucepan to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),(1,'Calamari in a Creamy White Wine Sauce','Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente; drain.'),(1,'Calamari Marinara','Drizzle olive oil into a saucepan. Add onions, chile pepper, garlic, anchovy filet, red pepper flakes, and salt; place over medium-high heat. Stir and cook until onions and garlic just start to turn golden, 3 or 4 minutes.'),(1,'California Italian Wedding Soup','Mix together beef, egg, bread crumbs, cheese, basil, parsley, and green onions; shape into 3/4-inch meatballs.'),(1,'California Roll','Gather all ingredients.'),(1,'Camp David Spaghetti with Italian Sausage','Slice the sausages lengthwise, leaving them attached along one side. Spread them out flat in a large skillet. Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, turning once, until the sausages are browned and cooked through. Remove from skillet and set aside.'),(1,'Cannoli','Make shells: Mix flour, sugar, and cinnamon together in a medium bowl. Cut in shortening until crumbly.'),(1,'Cannoli Cheesecake','Make the crust: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Line a 9-inch springform pan with parchment paper and lightly spray paper and sides of the pan with cooking spray.'),(1,'Caprese Salad with Balsamic Reduction','Stir balsamic vinegar and honey together in a small saucepan and place over high heat. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, and simmer until mixture has reduced to 1/3 cup, about 10 minutes. Set aside to cool.'),(1,'Caprese Salad with Grilled Flank Steak','Mix tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, 1 clove minced garlic, and 1 tablespoon olive oil in a bowl; toss to coat. Cover bowl and refrigerate.'),(1,'Carabaccia (Tuscan Onion Soup)','Make the soup: Peel onions and cut in half. Cut along the grain lengthwise into thin slices.'),(1,'Carrot Halwa','Melt ghee in a saucepan over medium heat. Add carrots; cook and stir until soft, about 5 minutes. Add milk and bring to a boil. Cook and stir until thickened, about 10 minutes. Reduce heat to medium.'),(1,'Carrot Recipe','In a saucepan over medium heat, combine carrots and milk. Bring to a boil, and cook until most of the milk evaporates, about 10 minutes. Stir in sugar, and simmer until mixture becomes dry. Stir constantly to ensure that it doesn\'t burn. Remove from heat.'),(1,'Carrot Rice','Combine rice and water in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low, cover with lid, and allow to steam until tender, about 20 minutes.'),(1,'Cauliflower and Potato Stir-Fry - East Indian Recipe','Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat; add cumin and caraway seeds until they begin to pop and oil bubbles, 1 to 2 minutes. Cook and stir onion and garlic in the hot oil until onion is soft and translucent, 5 to 10 minutes.'),(1,'Cauliflower Rice (Biryani-Style)','Process cauliflower florets in a blender or food processor until broken into small pieces about the size of rice.'),(1,'Cavatelli and Broccoli','Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Cook broccoli in boiling water for about 5 minutes. Use a slotted spoon to remove broccoli to a large bowl and set aside.'),(1,'Chai Tea','In a saucepan, bring water to a boil. Add the tea bags, cardamom seeds, cinnamon, and black pepper, then return to a boil. Immediately stir in sugar.'),(1,'Chai Tea Concentrate','Bring water to a boil in a saucepan; add cloves and boil for 1 minute. Add cinnamon sticks, ginger, cardamom pods, peppercorns, and tea. Allow tea to steep for 6 minutes; strain into a container. Stir brown sugar and vanilla extract into tea and refrigerate until chilled, at least 1 hour.'),(1,'Chai Tea Ice Cream','Mix whole milk, whipping cream, sugar, cinnamon sticks, tea, garam masala, peppercorns, cardamom pods, anise pods, and nutmeg together in a saucepan; bring to a simmer and cook for 20 minutes. Strain mixture through a colander into a large bowl. Add up to 1 cup more milk to cut spice level and sweetness to your liking.'),(1,'Chana Masala (Chickpeas and Tomatoes)','Heat oil in a 6-quart Dutch oven or large heavy pot over medium heat; sautÃ© onion until translucent, 5 to 10 minutes. Add garlic and sautÃ© until softened and fragrant, about 5 minutes. Add 1/4 cup water, coriander, paprika, ginger, turmeric, cayenne pepper, black pepper, and cinnamon to onion mixture. Cook and stir until fragrant, 2 to 3 minutes.'),(1,'Chana Masala (Savory Indian Chick Peas)','Grind onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, and chile pepper together in a food processor into a paste.'),(1,'Channa Masala (Chickpea Curry)','Combine the tomatoes, about half the onion, the ginger, and rice flour in a blender; blend into a paste.'),(1,'Cheese Lasagna','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),(1,'Cheesy Pol